# External Library APIs

Components: Zotero, Mendeley, PubMed, arXiv, Archive under `src/components/library/`.

## Fetch Discipline

- Always set request timeouts (AbortController) for third-party APIs.
- Handle non-2xx responses with user-visible error toasts; never throw unhandled rejections.
- Parse JSON defensively; validate required fields before `db` writes.

<example>
if (!response.ok) {
  toast.error(t('library.syncFailed'));
  return;
}
const data = await response.json();
if (!Array.isArray(data?.items)) return;
</example>

<example type="invalid">
const html = await response.text();
container.innerHTML = html; // XSS risk
</example>

## Rate Limits & Keys

- Respect NCBI/PubMed usage guidelines (email parameter where required).
- Zotero/Mendeley credentials come from user input or vault — never from env vars.
- Debounce search inputs; avoid request storms on keystroke.

## Local Persistence

- Map external metadata to `@src/types.ts` `Source` shape before `db.sources` insert.
- Deduplicate by stable external IDs where available.
- Store only metadata locally; PDF binaries use filesystem/OPFS flows in Research phase.

## UI

- Show loading and empty states for all async library operations.
- Disable submit while `fetch` is in flight.
